item.description:
Come watch the Audubon Society give a live owl presentation at Massabesic Audubon Center! Hear about the care and history of their female barred owl, as well as the behavior of these magnificent creatures in the wild. The audubon society will charge $3 for members and $5 for nonmembers for the owl presentation.

I'll be wearing a pink top and will greet you at the entrance to the center starting at 1:45.
The presentation will run from 2:00 until 2:30.

If you're only interested in the hike, we will be starting at 2:40. I'll be charging $1 for the hike to cover meetup expenses. I'll be guiding the group on a 1.5 mile gentle hike through the woods to the osprey blind ending in a hay field where I'd love to do some bird watching with anyone who is interested. (I've spotted blue birds, phoebes, goldfinches, and black-capped chickadees to name a few).

group.name: North Shore Not Too Intense Hikers

item.name: Live Owl Presentation followed by hike
